HEADWORD: Bespangle
<hw>Be*span"gle</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Bespangled</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Bespangling</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<def>To adorn with spangles; to dot or sprinkle with something brilliant
or glittering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The grass . . . is all <qex>bespangled</qex> with dewdrops.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bespangled</ent>⟦br⟧
